column2: Southwest wind 15 mph- clear sky- little boating past week- no weed spraying yet
E wind 10-15 mph- no boat activity
Southwest wind 10 mph- clear- partial weed kill 6/28- dredging inlet and holding ponds
Northeast wind 10-15 mph- overcast- no boats- no rain in 3 weeks.- 2nd phase of weed kill completed last week
Overcast- rain for 3 days- (3") - no boat activity- lake improving since weed spraying 2 weeks ago.
Southwest wind 10 mph- clear- heavy rain last night- no boat activity
Overcast- SW wind 10-15 mph- several days rain on + off- heavy suspended algae- heavy boat activity yesterday
Clear- SE wind 5 mph- heavy algae- lt. rain 2 days ago- one ski boat now
Cloudy- SW wind 10-15 mph- light boat activity past weekend- less algae
Overcast- calm- algae- no boats- unusual water color- rain almost daily past week
S wind 15-20 mph- clear sky- no boat activity
Clear- SW wind 10-15 mph- last report
Extremely heavy algae- early brown color- family of geese with 9 babies.  Water level: Up 3-4"
Cloudy- lt. SE breeze- heavy algae- no boats
Clear- NW wind 15-20 mph- weekend boating activity
Sunny- clear- SW wind 10-15 mph- some boat activity
Sunny- calm- no boats- some algae
Sunny- SW wind 10-15 mph- some boats- some algae
Hazy sun- SW wind 10-15 mph- some boat activity.  Water level: up 3"
Partly sunny- W wind 10-15 mph- heavy algae- no boats.  Water level: up 2"
Clear- SW wind 20 mph- no boats- heavy algae
Clear sky- calm- no boats- heavy algae
Sunny- SW wind 10 mph- no boats- heavy algae
Sunny- 90 F- algae- light breeze- unusual amount of weeds: spray before June.  Water level: up 3"
Sunny- 91 F- heavy algae- lake to be sprayed tomorrow- heavy boat traffic.  Water level: up 3"
Sunny- 80 F- northwest wind at 15-20 mph- heavy boat traffic- heavy algae- weeds controlled by spraying.
Algae worst in 20 years- weeds flourishing
Sunny- SW wind at 10-15 mph- some boat traffic- heavy algae and weeds
Sunny- a few clouds- SW wind at 15 mph- light boat traffic
Partly sunny- hazy- S wind at 10 mph- light boat traffic- 8th day of 90+ F weather- fishing poor.
Sunny- brisk SW winds- clouds over Lake Michigan- light boat traffic- 78 F
Partly sunny- northwest wind at 5 mph- 50 F- no boats out- thick algae bloom on 9/13 (after all day rain)
Sunny- calm- few fishermen- little boat traffic- Canada geese taking over
Sunny- W wind at 10 mph- water turning drab- geese all over lake.
Bright- sunny day- 64 degrees. No one on lake.
Sunny- 70 degrees. Strong winds last four days.
North shore is clear: rest of the lake has a lot of blue/green algae and scum.
Still have algae along shore- have been finding a number of good sized blue gills wash up on shore.
Received .75" of rain 6-17 but none since- algae still at shore but now also suspended in deep water.
Mostly sunny- no suspended algae in deep water but some along the shore.
Overcast day.  Light west wind.  No algae.  Have had heavy rains.
Mostly cloudy.  Light east wind.  Slight algae bloom.
Bright sun.  Light NW winds- temp is 66 degrees.  No algae.
Bright sun- wind is calm- temp is 63 degrees.  Light algae suspended in water- heavy algae along the south shore on 8-6-7.

A brown scum-like algae is forming on everything in the water- scum also floating in the water- have had 2 weeks of strong winds- very high water- much rain and cool temps- water was up 10" from norm.
Bright sun.  Light wind @ 5 mph.  There has been green algae floating along the shore.  Brown water color is getting lighter.  Temp is 73 degrees.
Bright and sunny- no clouds.  Wind is N @ 5 mph.  Had 30 -40 mph winds all day yesterday.  Water looks like coffee- but clear.
Bright sun- no clouds- west wind 15 mph- air temp 68.
Bright sun- N wind 5 mph- air temp 63- suspended algae- normal green color
Water turning brown again- we have suspended algae- still getting a lot of rain- partly sunny- 62.
Sunny- W wind 5 mph- suspended algae- air temp 71
Overcast- E wind 10 mph- storm 6/30 am- air temp 70- no suspended matter
Humid- sunny- air temp 75- calm wind- floating algae.
Bright sunny day- 73 F- had a 4-5" rainfall on 7-17- still have algae- floating + suspended.
50% cloudy- W wind 15 mph- air temp 65- I see no algae.
Very overcast- 71 degrees- east wind about 5 mph- have had humid days for the past week.
Bright hazy day- 50% cloud cover- W wind 5 mph- air temp 76- lots of suspended algae
Over cast day- 100%- wind is southwest. @ 5 mph.  Temp is 70 degrees- pea soup looking water- floating green scum.
Partly sunny- 50% clouds- wind is southwest. @ 10 mph.  Temp is 70 degrees- no floating algae.
Bright sunny - 30% clouds- temp is 51 degrees- wind is calm- temp was down to 41 degrees last night
Sunny- 50% clouds.  Temps 51 degrees.  Wind is south @ 15 mph- was 36.  Last night.
Partly sunny- 50% clouds- temperature is 66 degrees- wind north east @ 15 mph.  We had 80 degrees temperature yesterday.  It was 75 degrees at noon today.
Bright sunny day- 20% clouds- north east wind @ 5 mph. temp is 52 degrees.  I see large balls of algae that look like light green smoke clouds.
Bright sun- 5% clouds- wind is SW @ 5 mph- temp is 38 degrees- I still see large balls of light green smoke like clouds in the water.
Bright sun- no clouds- wind west 5 mph- temp. 41 degrees.  Ice went out 3-25-94.

Bright sunny day- no clouds- strong wind south-southwest 25 mph- had much rain yesterday till 4 am this morning.  Lots of lightning- heavy coat of green algae along south shore.  Also scum like moss on shallow weeds.
Bright sun 40% clouds- light NE wind 5 mph- temp. 50 degrees.  I see a lot of cotton-like algae on the bottom.
Partly sunny 50% clouds- temp. 66 degrees- wind N 10 mph.  Still have moss-like green matter covering weeds + bottom.
Partly sunny 40% clouds- wind NE 10 mph- temp. 72 degrees.  I see suspended algae- also a heavy mat of green algae all along most of shore line to 50 ft. out.  Have had no rain in past week.
Sunny 10% clouds- wind NE 10 mph- temp. 62 degrees.  Most of algae floating mat has gone over last 5 days- but still see suspended algae in deep water.  Many big carp snorting on bottom near shore.

Overcast 90% clouds- wind is SW @ 20 mph- temp is 73 degrees- have been seeing more dead pan fish than normal- our floating algae was gone for about 5 days- then came back- this time patches of blue green algae- first rain in 10 days last
Bright hazy day- 10% clouds- wind west 15 mph- temp. 89 degrees.  Most algae along shore gone.  Had good rain last night-~ .5".  Has been very warm for over a week.
Partly sunny- 50% clouds- wind N 10 mph- temp. 77 degrees.  South + west shore has a lot of algae along shore.  On 2-27 we had about 5 acres of lake treated with Cutrine plus for algae.
Bright hazy day- 30% clouds- wind NW 10 mph- temp. 82 degrees- a high of 95 degrees yesterday.  We have an algae mat along SW + s. shore.  Have a lot of floating algae on southern side of lake.
Mostly cloudy- 75% clouds- temp. 66 degrees- wind north 10 mph.  I see no floating algae or mat along shore.  But the lake bottom + growing weeds are full of it.
Mostly overcast- 80% clouds temperature 72 degrees- wind SW @ 5 mph- had about .5" of rain last night- we still have algae stuck to plants and on the bottom- the bottom water sample did smell
100% overcast- temp. 69 degrees- wind NW 5 mph.  Still have algae on bottom + growing plants.  Also large mats are forming on top.

Bright sunny day- 0% clouds- wind north-northeast. @ 5 mph- temp is 62 degrees- has been very cool in the last 10 days.  Only algae is on the bottom and on the plants- have had a lot of rain- bottom water is smelly
Mostly sunny- 25% clouds- temp. 70 degrees- wind SW 5 mph.  Only algae I see is near inlet- but still on plants + bottom.
Sunny- 50% clouds- temp. 60 degrees- wind NE 5 mph.  The week has been cool + weed growth has slowed down.
Bright hazy day- 0% clouds- wind is w-southwest @ 10 mph- temperature is 68 degrees- it has been warm this past week.  Trees are starting to show colors and the acorns dropping like hail
Partly sunny- 50 % clouds- wind W 20 mph- temp. 55 degrees.  Last 5 days have been cool.  Almost no boat traffic past week.  Had light rain the past 5 days.
Sunny- 10 % clouds- wind S 15 mph- temp. 62 degrees.  The temp. has been down to 40 degrees at night.

Bright sun- no clouds- wind is south at 10 mph.  Temp is 52 degrees- we have had frost the last two nights- yesterday the temp was 62 degrees- lots of color in the trees.  There is some algae on the bottom near our inlet (3 Ft)
100% overcast- wind west 10 mph- temp. 58 degrees.  The color in the trees have peaked- + dropping like rain.
50% sun-wind east 10 mph.  Temp. 50 degrees.  Ice went out on 3-16-95.  I see pieces of algae floating on 12th-13-14-15-+ 16th.  Temp. was over 65 degrees.
Overcast.  No sun.  Wind NW 15 mph.  Temp. 42 degrees.  It has been about 40 degrees the last 10 days or so.
Overcast- 100%.  Wind is SE @ 20 mph- temp is 44 degrees- have had a lot of rain the past 2 days.  We are getting snow pellets today- as yet- no dead fish along the shore.
Sunny- 10% clouds.  Wind SW 5 mph.  Temp. 65 degrees.  Cotton candy shaped algae forming on bottom.
Turn over.  30% clouds.  Wind calm.  Temp. 72 degrees.  We have a lot of algae on bottom + shallow weeds.  Lake is having massive weed growth.
30% clouds + hazy.  Wind SE 5 mph- temp. 75 degrees.  We have suspended particles in water.
West wind- 5 mph- 100% clear- no clouds.  Temp is 75 degrees- still see many small particles suspended in water.  The lake does not seem to be as clear as the secchi would indicate.
Bright hazy day 50% clouds- temp 77 degrees.  Wind S 5 mph.  We had about .5" rain yesterday.
Temp. 76 degrees- wind SW 10 mph.  Mostly cloudy- 30% sun.  We had a lot of boat traffic the past weekend.
Bright sun- 5% clouds- temp. 80 degrees- wind east 3 mph.  We have slight algae on south shore.
Wind SW 5 mph.  Hazy but no clouds.  Temp 76 degrees- our weeds seemed dormant during past hot spell but are now growing.
Wind west 5 mph.  Overcast- 10% sun.  Temp 62 degrees.  It was 48 degrees at 6:30 this morning.  Have had very little rain and much cooler last 2 weeks.
Wind W almost calm- clear day- no clouds- temp. 68 degrees.  We had a killing frost on 9-22-95.
Temp is 50 degrees- sunny- 15% clouds- wind is W @ 15 mph.  The lake was 2" low two weeks ago- we have algae growth on all the weeds on bottom.
Brown at shore - green in deep water. temp. 50 degrees. bright sunny day- 10 % clouds- wind S 2 mph.  Almost calm. I see dark green balls of algae.
Lake is brown at shore- but green in deep water. Bright sunny day. No clouds. Wind west at 10 mph. Temp. 60 degrees. Lot of rain the last 2 days.
Temp. 58 degrees. Bright sun- no clouds- wind east- almost calm- have a lot of floating and suspended algae.
Hazy bright day. Wind west 5 mph. Temp. 68 degrees. A lot of algae floating along shoreline.
Water green- clear. 50% clouds. Wind N 10 mph. Temp. 79 degrees- weed growth tremendous!
Wind SW 10 mph. 50% clouds. Temp. 79 degrees. The weeds around rim of lake are almost out of control! We are seeing many carp!
Wind W @ 10 mph- temp is 70 degrees- bright clear day- had about .5" of rain fall yesterday- still have mats of algae stuck on weeds along the shore area.
Wind SW 10 mph. Temp. 75 degrees. Bright day 20% clouds. We have a lot of green algae along shoreline.
Wind NW 10 mph- temp. 70 degrees- 100% overcast. have had cool days. We have algae along shore.
Temp. 78 degrees- wind S 10 mph. Bright sunny day 15% clouds.
Bright but hazy day- 50 % clouds. Wind west 15 mph- temp. 77 degrees- no algae.
Wind W @ 5 mph- temp is 78 degrees- mostly overcast.  Lots of boat traffic the weekend previous to sample
Bright sunny day- 5% clouds- wind south-southwest 5 mph- temp. 77 degrees.
Wind calm- 30% clouds- bright but hazy. Temp. 80 degrees. I see algae forming along shoreline.
Wind west almost calm 2 mph. Bright sunny day. 10 % clouds. Temp. 68 degrees. Oak trees look stressed.
Wind NNW 5 mph. Bright day. No clouds. Temp. 59 degrees. Need rain badly. We have had very cool + dry days.
Wind NNW 15 mph. Bright clear day. 20% clouds. Temp. 58 degrees. We need rain.
Bright sunny day. 5% clouds. Wind SW 20 mph. Temp. 69 degrees. Had about 1" rainfall last week.
Bright sunny day- 50% clouds.  Wind is west @ 5 mph.  Temp is 45 degrees- no killing frost yet- but leaves are turning.  Top sample- no depth reported- assumed 3'.
Bright clear day. 5% clouds. Wind SW 10 mph. Temp. 72 degrees. Got first killing frost on the 10th.
Partly sunny- 30% cloud cover.  Temperature 52 degrees.  Strong wind from the northeast at 20 mph.  Has been very cold.
Overcast with about 70% clouds.  Wind calm.  We have had many days of strong NE winds.  Some suspended algae.  Weeds are growing.
No sun- 100% overcast.  Wind from SW at 4 mph.  Temperature 75 degrees.  We have too many weeds and too many Canada geese.
Bright sun about 3% clouds.  Wind SW at 10 mph.  88 degrees.  Has been very warm the past week.  I think our swimmers itch is over now.
Wind east about 10 mph. Bright day but 75% clouds.  Temperature 74 degrees.
Bright clear day.  60% cloud cover.  Temperature 76 degrees.  Wind NNW at 10 mph.  We have very thick weed growth.

100% overcast.  Rained until 11:30 A.M.  Wind south at 5 mph/  70 degrees.  We had rain most of yesterday but only about 1/2 inch.  Rained until almost noon today.  May try to get another weed harvest done next week- they are thick.
Sunny day.  40% clouds.  Wind SW at 5 mph.  Temperature 64 degrees.  Has been cool and rainy.  Water looks good but weedy.
15%  clouds- wind southeast at 10 mph- temperature was 75 degrees

Bright sunny day- about 5% clouds. calm.  58 degrees.  On September 16th we got 2.5 inches of rain.  Than on the 19th we got 2 inches of rain from a very bad storm.  We went from four inches low on the 16th to six inches high on the 20th.
West wind at 5 mph with 5% clouds. The temperature is 70 degrees.
Wind NE at 5 mph.  Sunny 50% clouds.  55 degrees.
SE wind 10 mph. Sunny 100% clear. 76 degrees.
W wind 15 mph. Sunny 30% clouds. 83 degrees.
E wind 15 mph.  Sunny 15% clouds.  70 degrees.
Bright and sunny. Wind SW 15 mph. 90 degrees.
Northeast wind at 5 mph.  100% overcast. 78 degrees.
W wind at 15 mph. Overcast 80 degrees.
E wind 2 mph. 80% clear.  Algae floating and suspended. 74 degrees.
Ne wind at 5 mph 67 degrees.  Sunny 9% clear.
Calm and sunny.  No clouds.  69 degrees.  Floating algae.
Sunny- 50% clouds- calm wind- temp is 55 degrees- no dead fish after winter- and geese are back.
Bright sun with no clouds- calm wind- temp is 70 degrees- water yellow at shore- and much suspended algae.
Bright but hazy day with no sun- SE wind 10 mph- temp is 70 degrees- blue green algae at shore- and lots of rain.
Bright sun- 5% clouds- NW wind 8 mph- temp 67 degrees- and we had a 3" rain fall yesterday.
Bright sun with no cloudy- west wind 10 mph- temp is 78 degrees- and we have a lot of floating algae.
Bright but overcast- had rain 8:30 am- lot of floating algae + weeds- wind west- 76 F.
Bright- sunny- temp 93 F- wind SW 5 mph- has been very hot- weeds are bad.
Bright- sunny- temp 65 F- wind NW 10 mph- has been hot last 5 days 90+
The wind is south- overcast- algae at shore- temperature is 65 degrees- and had 3" of rainfall on the 18th.
The wind is west- sunny- 88 degrees- floating algae on lake- and I see some smaller dead fish.
The wind is south- temperature is 68 degrees- have floating algae- and I still see some smaller dead fish.
The wind is north- temperature is 81 degrees- bright but hazy- and south shore looks like pea soup.
The wind is west- mostly sunny- the temperature is 80 degrees- and a lot of boat traffic this past weekend.
The wind is calm- mostly cloudy- temperature is 70 degrees- and I no longer see small dead fish by the shore.
Calm- clear- 78 degrees- and few clouds.
The wind is north at 8 mph- temperature is 75 degrees- partly cloudy- and it rained heavily two days prior to reading.
The wind is southeast at about 8 mph- temperature is 77 degrees- and mostly cloudy overcast.
The wind is south at 10 mph- 75 degrees- slight overcast and sunny.
Wind SW 5 mph- temp-65 deg. F- mostly cloudy- no rain 5 days prior.
Clear.  Sunny.  East wind.  65 F.  No rain few days.  Some algae.
Clear.  Sunny.  No clouds.  SE wind 5 mph.  73 F.  No rain few days.  Some algae.
Mostly sunny.  SE wind 8 mph.  80 F.  No rain all week.
Clear.  Sunny.  No clouds.  NW wind 5 mph.  80 F.  No rain 2 weeks.
Sunny.  No clouds.  SE wind 5 mph.  83 F.  No rain few days.
Mostly sunny.  Few clouds.  NE wind 2 mph.  70 F.  Rain 3 days ago.
Light breeze NW.  Mostly sunny.  Light thin clouds (few).  Rained hard day before.
Sunny.  NE wind 2 mph.  Clear sky.  70 F.  Lots of rain previous week.
Partly sunny.  NW wind 15 mph.  50 F.  Cold front came in day before.
Partly sunny. SW wind 10 mph.  60 F.
Clear- no clouds- West winds at 5 mph- air temp 80 degrees F and some algae.
Mostly cloudy- some breaks of sun- SW winds at 10 mph- air and water temps =70 degrees F.
Mostly sunny- slight haze- SW winds at 5 mph- air temp =85 degrees F- and some algae.
Overcast with NE 8 mph wind. Air tmap= 76 degrees F.
mostly overcast and 82F. S winds at 5 mph. Rained the night before.
mostly sunny- wind SW 8mph- water 78F- air 81F.
Partly sunny- slight west wind- water and air temps are 75 degrees F.
sunny with slight south wind and air temp of 82F.
Sunny- air temp = 68 degrees F- and east winds at 8 mph.
sunny with slight haze- NE wind 5mph.
west wind 8mph- 78F temp- sunny with slight haze.
North 5mph- 70F- mostly sunny- rain day before.
west 5mph- 85 F- haze and partly cloudy.
Overcast to partly cloudy- NE 5mph- temp is 67F.
Sunny- 65-70- light chop- lots of loons- one cormorant
Northeast wind at 10mph- 60F with overcast- much rain the previous week.  Lake level highest in last 5 years.
Northwest wind at 5mph- 67 F air temperature- clear sky- been cool last couple days.
Northeast wind at 2mph- air temperature was 72F- water temperature was 71F- mostly clear with some high thin clouds.
Southeast wind at 8mph- 70F air temp- party cloudy with high haze- cooler than normal.
West wind at 5mph- 71F outdoor air temperature- cloudy and mostly overcast- cooler than norm.
Slight wind from north- 67 F air temp- clear and sunny.
west by southwest 5mph- 71F water- 75F air- mostly overcast-52.8F at 30 feet- and 69.8F at 12 feet.
Northwest wind 5mph- mostly sunny- 65F air temp- 52.8F at 30 feet and 69.6F at 3 feet.
Sunny with no clouds- north wind 10 mph- 62 F air temperature- rained all day the day before.
East wind at 5mph- partly cloudy- and 65F air temperature.
Light SE wind- completely sunny- been very dry with little rain in last few weeks- and 75 F air temperature.
South wind- very light- mostly cloudy- 80 F air temperature- been hot during last few days.
Light east wind- sunny and no clouds- very dry for past many weeks- 80 F air temperature.
Light east wind- mostly sunny with some light clouds- very dry- and about 77F.
Light south wind- partly sunny- been very dry- lake low by about 8 inches- 70F.
Southeast wind at 8mph- mostly overcast- very dry- lake is very low- 84F.
Strong wind NE 10mph- mostly cloudy with some sun- 65F- rain night before.
Clear sunny morning with a 5mph south wind- 70F air temp and 77.7F water temp- no rain for a few days.
Wind north at 5mph- mostly overcast- 75F air temp- rain day before.
Mostly sunny- 78F outside temperature- rain morning day before- light NE wind.
mostly sunny- 70F outside air temp- light east wind- water temp 78F.
Wind SE at 5 mph- cloudy- 80 F air temperature- light rain day before- water 76 F.
NE wind at 10mph- cloudy all day- 65F airtemp- water at 73F- very cool.
Clear sunny day- 70F outside air- light west wind.
Light wind SE 5mph- mostly sunny- 65 F- no rain for few days.
Strong wind East 10mph- mostly high overcast with some sun- 61F- rough lake.
Moderate wind southwest at 5mph; 68F; mostly sunny; no rain for a few days.
Light south wind at 5mph- sunny- 68F- no rain for a couple days.
Moderate wind NW at 5mph- outside air temperature 75F- some patches of sun- rain night before.
Moderate wind NE at 5 mph- 70F outside temperature- 76F water temperature- mostly sunny.
Moderate east wind at 5 to 10 mph- 75F outside air- mostly overcast- with rain a few days earlier.

Light south wind- 75 F air temp- completely sunny- no rain in 5-days but at least 8 inches of rain the week before.  Heavy amount of water enterring the lake with lake shut down for travel for most of prior week.
North wind at about 5mph- sunny- air temperature 52F- no rain all week- very cool nights last couple.
Light southwest wind- 75F air temperature- sunny- lake looks great - no weeds on surface.
Wind northwest at 10mph; mostly sunny; no rain in few days.
Wind south at 5 mph- light overcast- 65F outside temp- little boat traffic due to cool spring.
Wind SW at 5mph- perfectly sunny- lots of rain during week; temp 70F.
Strong wind 10 to 15 mph from West- sunny- lots of rain last few days- outside temperature is 70F.
Wind west 5 mph- sunny and clear- been dry for past few days- lots of algae on southwest side of lake.
Wind out of Northwest at 5mph- 70F- mostly sunny and no rain during previous week.  Did weed harvesting earlier in the week.
Wind east at 8-10 mph- 65 F outside temperature- overcast- with rain day before.
Wind from east at 5 to 10 mph- mostly cloudy- rain expected later today- 65 F outside temperature- sunny day before.
Wind was NE at 5 mph- with mostly cloudy- 70 F outside temperature- and weather has been rather cool for start of summer.
Sunny and completely clear- 70F outside temperature- northwest wind 5mph- and had rain night before.
Wind west at 5 mph- mostly overcast- 70F outside- rained hard yesterday late afternoon.
Wind out of south at 10mph with stronger gusts- completely sunny- rained most of day before- 85 F outside temperature- very humid- had weed harvester out this past week for 2-days of weed cutting.
Wind light out of north- sunny- been cool previous few days- only 70F outside air temperature.
Wind light from west- nice and sunny- no rain in about 15 days- 70F outside temp.
Clear sunny day with 5mph wind from west- heavy rain storm day before with high winds- about 74F.
Sunny and warm- outside temperature about 80F- been very warm the past week with temperatures reaching above 90F- wind west at 5mph.  No rain for a few days.
Been cooler at nights past few days- completely sunny past two days mid to upper 70's F-  wind East to SE at 5 to 10mph- air temp is 65F.
Nice fairly warm day for a change- 70F- NE wind 5 to 10 mph- partly cloudy- been very windy for past week or so with winds out of north by northeast.
Perfect day with approximate 5mph wind out of east- 70F air temperature- dry last couple days- however been fairly cool for about a week.
Wind from east at about 5mph- rained fairly good on Monday July 11th- but been very dry for over 3-weeks- partly cloudy- and OD temperature 70F.

Very sunny with west wind about 5 to 10 mph- 75 F outside- had rain day before.  Been very dry most days with heavy rain then coming once in awhile.  Lake in great shape with use of chemicals and weed harvesting.
Excellent sunny day with mild breeze from north at about 5mph- 65F outside temperature.  Last few days been quite windy with little rain in past few weeks.
Partly cloudy with a southeast wind at 5mph.  Been very dry with no rain over a week.  Harvesting and chemical treatments have been done in past couple weeks.
Outstanding day- perfectly clear- with north to northwest wind about 5mph.  No rain in over two weeks and been very hot - in the 90's F almost every day last couple weeks.
Nice sunny day with 5mph wind from south by southeast- been dry a bit for past couple months with only some rain coming in past two weeks.  Lake very low for the season.
Nice sunny day with light wind from west- about 70 F.  Rained all day the day before but light rain.  Hasn't been as hot past few weeks.
Slight overcast- no rain in about 4 days- southwest wind about 10mph- with rain expected this afternoon.
Quite windy today and been warm last few days- mid-80's- partly to mostly cloudy today- with outside temperature of 75F- wind south at 10mph.
Partly cloudy- cool with strong winds previous evening.  Outside temperature is 65F- wind NE at 10mph with gusts to 18mph.
Humidity finally coming down- rain yesterday about 1/2 inch- mostly sunny with puffy white clouds- 75F outside with wind out of west at 5mph.
Filtered sun- with slight haze- about 85F and been hot for few days- going into mid-90's today.  Wind 8mph from southwest.  Lake looks great.

Beautiful day with mostly sunny and some puffy white clouds- OD temperature about 65F and wind out of NE at approximately 10mph.  Was hot earlier in week with temps high in 90's.  All surface weeds have disappeared due to the high winds yesterday and today.  Nice looking.
Outstanding day with few puffy white clouds- light breeze out of south by southwest- temperature about 80F- lake is quiet today but was busy last couple days due to nice warm days.
Outstanding day with light breeze out of east- about 75F outside temperature- a few puffy clouds- and temperature has been around 75F for last few days.  No rain for a few days either.

No clouds today with slight minor haze- 75 F outside temperature- wind about 5mph from west- and no rain in about a week.  Been cooler overall in July and continues that way into August.  Some flocks of geese seen on the lake lately.  Passing through hopefully.

Very nice day with slight haze- wind out of west at 5mph- outside temperature about 80F- with last major rain on Saturday.  Lake looks good with some weeds hanging on surface.  Harvester to be here this week to cut weeds along the shore.

Nice day with breeze out of southeast at about 5mph- mostly sunny with some clouds coming in from west.  Been cool at night so great sleeping.  Lake in pretty good shape since did two harvestings and a number of chemical treatments.
Quite windy- East NE at about 10mph- but mostly sunny.  Had a day of rain the day before.  Weeds are not too bad on the lake right now.  Nice boating conditions.
Nice day after two to three inches of rain over past 4 days.  Sunny with slight breeze from NE- about 70 F outside.

Mostly sunny with 5 mph wind out of NNE- about 70 F and few puffy white clouds starting to move in.  Mostly cloudy the day before and 2-days before got about 1.5 inches of rain.  Weeds are not growing too badly this year and harvesting and chemicals continue to be used around the lake.

Outstanding day on the lake with light wind from northeast- mostly sunny with puffy white clouds.  Temperature about 80F.  Rained about 1/2 inch on Sunday.  Lake in great shape but water level down about 6 inches.
Been quite warm the past few days and mighty warm today with high humidity.  Wind out of SE at less than 5mph with outside temperature about 85F.  Partly cloudy.
Light overcast with 5mph wind out of south- been very nice the past 4 days with temperatures in the 70's.  Outdoor temperature currently is 70F and going into 80's today.

Lake is in great shape after a fairly warm winter- temperature today about 65F- wind out of northeast very light- few fluffy clouds and lots of sun.  Been in 70's for past week of so- but was in mid-40's yesterday!

Another very warm day with temperature about 80 F early in morning.  Wind is blowing fairly good from southwest at about 10mph.  Been in upper 80's past few days with little rain for weeks.  Lake looks nice and is being used a lot- but weeds are growing fast.
Very warm last few days with no rain- wind out of southeast and light- air temperature is 80 F.  Mostly sunny with a slight haze. lily pads growing too much!
Nice clear sunny day with slight 5mph breeze out of southwest.  Had been very warm the past week and got a couple inches of rain a few days ago- but lake in wonderful condition.
